The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 07 November is 6,647 (769.3 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 02 November, there were 833 new confirmed cases (96.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 26 October, there were 818 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 2% ( 15 extra cases).
